# Wish list.
#
# Effort tags: XS = a few lines / one-shot · S = small, one layer · M = a
# session, multiple layers · L = full feature (DB+API+realtime+UI) · XL = major
# project / new security model. Backlog is sorted by effort, lowest first.
# "→" marks a decision worth making before the work starts.

## Done

- Hide disabled users from the roster ordinary users see (admins still see them).
- Drop the member button/list in DMs.
- Refresh display name / avatar when they change (live, no refresh).
- Let members leave a private channel; mods+ may remove others.
- In DMs, either participant may pin/unpin.
- Semver + About dialog. Version constant (config.Version), surfaced via
  /api/instance and an About modal opened from the sidebar brand.
- Durable notifications + opt-in desktop notifications (earlier work).
- Mute channels/DMs (durable, cross-device; full silence) — v0.9.1.
- Suppress historical "deleted" tombstones; only live-session deletes tombstone — v0.9.2.
- Update-available banner via a WS hello{version} handshake — v0.9.3.
- Admin stats panel (user/channel/message counts + live connections) — v1.0.0.

## Backlog (sorted by effort)

1. [M] Mobile: swipe right opens the channel drawer, left opens members.
   Drawer machinery (openDrawer/closeDrawers) already exists; this is the touch
   handling (touchstart/move/end) with thresholds, the tricky part being a
   horizontal swipe vs. vertical scroll. Frontend only.

2. [M] Typing indicators.
   Requires building the inbound-WS path (the read pump currently discards client
   frames). Client sends throttled "typing" frames; the hub relays to the channel
   audience; UI shows "X is typing…" with a timeout. Ephemeral, no DB.

3. [M] Autocomplete for @-pings (searchable by display name).
   Composer popup: on "@", filter the already-loaded users by username OR display
   name, insert the username. No backend. Fiddly bits: caret tracking, popup
   placement, keyboard nav.

4. [M→L] Every message timestamp links to that point in history.
   Needs a store query for a window *around* a message id (today's pagination is
   before-only keyset), a URL/hash scheme, and on open: load that window, scroll
   to + highlight the anchor. The jump primitive #5 reuses — do this first.

5. [M→L] Search.
   Message search scoped to channels the caller can access. Postgres full-text
   (to_tsvector + GIN index), an endpoint with pagination, and a results UI that
   jumps to a hit (reuses #4's permalink/jump).

6. [L] Custom emojis.
   Storage (a bytes-blob table + shortcode, like avatars), upload/manage endpoints
   (admin?), and :shortcode: rendering in format.js that PRESERVES its escape-first
   XSS invariant. A picker is the nice-to-have.

7. [L] Reactions.
   reactions(message_id, user_id, emoji) + add/remove endpoints + realtime
   reaction.add/remove + aggregation into the message payload/state + UI. Touches
   every layer. Pairs naturally with #6.

8. [XL] OTR / end-to-end encrypted messaging.
   The big one and a different security model: client-side crypto, key
   generation/exchange, key + trust management (and multi-device), server storing
   only ciphertext, verification UI. Signal/OMEMO class — wants its own design pass.

